### Interview
Q: What do you want your lane to do?
A: Simple escrow service. Holds funds from a depositor until release conditions are met, then allows recipient to claim. Supports refunds back to depositor if funds haven't been released yet. Core endpoints: create escrow, release, refund. Basic validation and minimal audit trail.

Q: What should the release condition be?
A: Depositor manually authorizes the release. Only the depositor can trigger release. Once released, only the recipient can claim. No time-based or external triggers. Keep it simple.

Q: What name do you want for your lane?
A: simple-escrow

Q: How should the audit trail be stored?
A: Simple log in K/V. List of events with timestamps — "escrow created", "funds released", "refund issued". Keep it minimal.

Q: Requirements summary confirmed?
A: Yes, confirmed.

